<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="97" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="13.[806,1421,236,381]" pageId="13" pageNumber="97">Mesoscutum covered with mixed long yellow and black hairs; fasciae clearly reaching lateral margins of tergites (or ending just before the lateral margin, but the lateral margin is always partly yellow).</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[806,1421,424,477]" pageId="13" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis box="[806,919,424,445]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="97">Genitalia:</emphasis>
Ventral margin of surstylus less concave than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Giglio-Tos" authorityYear="1890" box="[902,1030,455,476]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Chrysotoxum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="festivum">
<emphasis box="[902,1030,455,476]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="97">C. festivum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1093,1262,455,477]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Chrysotoxum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tomentosum">
<emphasis box="[1093,1262,455,477]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="97">C. tomentosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[806,1422,521,635]" box="[806,894,521,542]" pageId="13" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis box="[806,894,521,542]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="97">Habitat</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[806,1422,521,635]" pageId="13" pageNumber="97">
Deciduous forest/open ground, mesophilous/thermophilous deciduous forest and dry, unimproved grassland with scrub, on well-drained sites (
<bibRefCitation author="Speight MCD" box="[1249,1410,613,635]" pageId="13" pageNumber="97" refId="ref11297" refString="Speight MCD. 2012. Species accounts of European Syrphidae (Diptera), 2012. Syrph the Net, the database of European Syrphidae. Dublin: Syrph the Net publications." type="book" year="2012">Speight, 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[806,1421,679,823]" box="[806,878,679,700]" pageId="13" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis box="[806,878,679,700]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="97">Range</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[806,1421,679,823]" pageId="13" pageNumber="97">
Fennoscandia south to 
<collectingCountry box="[1072,1140,709,731]" name="Georgia" pageId="13" pageNumber="97">Iberia</collectingCountry>
and the Mediterranean; through central and southern Europe into European parts of 
<collectingCountry box="[900,977,770,792]" name="Russia" pageId="13" pageNumber="97">Russia</collectingCountry>
as far as the Caucasus Mountains and into 
<collectingCountry box="[861,942,801,823]" name="Turkey" pageId="13" pageNumber="97">Turkey</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Speight MCD" box="[959,1123,801,823]" pageId="13" pageNumber="97" refId="ref11297" refString="Speight MCD. 2012. Species accounts of European Syrphidae (Diptera), 2012. Syrph the Net, the database of European Syrphidae. Dublin: Syrph the Net publications." type="book" year="2012">Speight, 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
